The Servant [1963]

This film takes a sharp look at British class relations via a dramatic turning
of the tables between a dainty Oxbridge twit bachelor and his contemptuous
manservant. The servant slowly realizes and exploits his expanding powers over
his "master" as the twit steadily loses his authority and becomes enslaved to
his own "employee".    

Starring: Dirk Bogarde, Sarah Miles, Wendy Craig. Introducing James Fox.
Director: Joseph Losey
